-- French Socialists May Push For Musca as ESM Head, Le Figaro Says
-- B y   H e l e n e   F o u q u e t
-- 2012-03-24T09:16:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/french-socialists-may-push-for-musca-as-esm-head-le-figaro-says.html
France  may support the appointment
of Xavier Musca at the helm of the future European Stability
Mechanism if the Socialist candidate wins the next presidential
election,  Le Figaro daily  reported, without citing anyone.  Musca, President  Nicolas Sarkozy ’s chief of staff and top
economic advisor, would be the French candidate for the ESM’s
presidency if Socialist Party candidate  Francois Hollande  is
successful in the May presidential election.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helene Fouquet in Paris at 
